{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016AmygirDMZJYQiPUwZuTCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ingress-nginx is now being installed. Now I need to:\n1. Create a TLS secret for es.example.com\n2. Create an Ingress resource\n\nLet me create a self-signed TLS certificate for es.example.com. I'll use openssl to generate it. The openssl-toolbox pod is already running in the elasticsearch namespace.\n\nActually, I can generate the cert on the host directly using openssl.\n\nLet me also think about the backend configuration:\n- ES uses HTTPS on port 9200\n- I need to tell nginx to proxy to HTTPS backend\n- I need to disable SSL verification for the backend (since it uses self-signed certs)\n- I'm configuring the ingress annotations to set the backend protocol to HTTPS, disable SSL verification for the backend, and enable SSL redirects\n\nBut wait, I'm seeing conflicting information—the oracle comment mentions ES serving plain HTTP on 9200, but the actual configuration shows HTTPS. Let me check what's actually running.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_read_input_tokens":56568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":812},"output_tokens":42,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"2bb274ed-9f35-41d6-bcbd-a21402e8a850","request_id":"req_011Cc6mv17n2skGJg2cDAJVL"}
