{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMmomgqd2xJHfwKn9byV9y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ES cluster is in a partially-started state. es-2 is getting elected as master but failing to commit cluster state because \"node is no longer master\". This is probably because es-0 and es-1 are still running with the old configuration.\n\nThe cluster has mixed old (es-0, es-1 with old password env) and new (es-2 with new password env) nodes. Since all 3 nodes are in the cluster, there's master election conflict.\n\nActually - the key issue is that es-2 restarted and joined the cluster as a different node (it may have gotten a new node ID after restart). This caused master election issues.\nThe 503 response is troubling since it shows the HTTP API is up but the cluster itself isn't healthy enough to handle requests. I should give the cluster some time to stabilize and elect a proper master before checking the status again.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":989,"cache_read_input_tokens":65351,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":989},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"41297c5c-07f7-4722-a920-1881cec255eb","request_id":"req_011Cc6nJqq4uQXqthagmNBD1"}
