{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xb2MPMg9hevKQjjYQnBDbe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ES cluster can't find a master. This is because es-2 was restarted with a new node ID (the ephemeral ID or node ID changed). The cluster is trying to elect a master but can't form a quorum.\n\nThe cluster has 3 nodes. When es-2 restarted, it got a new node ID. But the other 2 nodes (es-0, es-1) still have the old cluster state. They might not recognize the new es-2.\n\nActually wait - ES StatefulSet uses PVCs for data. When es-2 was restarted, it kept its PVC data, which includes its node identity. \n\nSo the node ID should have persisted through the restart. Looking at the logs, es-2 is completing election with the same node ID that's in the discovery seed hosts, so it's definitely the same node. The real problem is the `master_not_discovered_exception` - the cluster can't form a quorum because with 3 nodes, you need at least 2 healthy ones to elect a master. If es-0 and es-1 aren't in good shape, es-2 alone can't make it happen. I need to check what's going on with those other two nodes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":462,"cache_read_input_tokens":66340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":462},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"d0027e2b-9923-4895-bb1c-d094857c7d7a","request_id":"req_011Cc6nNqAEymx8mShGay3Cd"}
