ment variables showing as `<none>` are from the init container, not the main container—I need to check the actual ES container's environment to understand what's happening. The sysctl init container is still in a Running state even though it should have completed quickly after setting the vm.max_map_count parameter, which is blocking the main Elasticsearch container from starting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1061,"cache_read_input_tokens":68316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1061},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"bcb36987-3a71-4f83-8d17-95a544d57fac","request_id":"req_011Cc6nTUb8XQ8k8yZgnGXQ4"}
