{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JgcdidZeDbeBZtfaiq227y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `configuration-snippet` annotation is disabled. This is a security feature in newer nginx ingress versions (it can be enabled with `--allow-snippet-annotations=true` flag, but it's disabled by default for security).\n\nI need a different approach. Let me think about alternatives:\n\n1. **Enable snippet annotations** on the ingress-nginx controller (by patching the deployment args)\n2. **Disable ES security** (update configmap and restart)\n3. **Use nginx auth proxy** via external auth service\n4. **Create a proxy Secret to inject headers** (using `proxy-set-headers` configmap)\n5. **Use the proxy-set-headers ConfigMap approach** to inject Authorization headers directly into requests sent to the backend\n\nThe `proxy-set-headers` annotation lets me reference a ConfigMap containing additional headers to pass through. I could create a ConfigMap with the Authorization header and reference it in the ingress, which would inject the credentials without needing snippet annotations.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1005,"cache_read_input_tokens":84515,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1005},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"123fab85-cbe5-4789-9511-bc61f15308b3","request_id":"req_011Cc6ni7dUAgUNsPtjx6jqf"}
