{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01D5vrKwYxsKdvU26ZWufyTq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ES is rolling out in RollingUpdate order. es-0 and es-1 are Ready (1/1). es-2 is the newest (just updated, 4m14s ago), and it's currently waiting for its readiness probe to pass.\n\nThe readiness probe still uses HTTPS: `curl -sk -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health`. But now security is disabled, so:\n1. ES is listening on plain HTTP (not HTTPS)\n2. The probe uses HTTPS and -sk (skip cert verification), but ES is on HTTP now\n3. The probe will fail because it's trying to connect via HTTPS to an HTTP port\n\nI need to update the StatefulSet to change the readiness probe to use HTTP instead. But updating the spec will trigger another rolling restart of all the pods.\n\nThe issue is that with `-k` flag, curl still attempts a TLS handshake when given an HTTPS URL. If the server is only listening on plain HTTP, that handshake will fail immediately, so the probe won't work regardless of the `-k` flag.\n\nI need to fix the readiness probe in the StatefulSet to use HTTP instead of HTTPS.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":594,"cache_read_input_tokens":88800,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":594},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"647e5713-95e1-44af-8c9c-398b1999fb5d","request_id":"req_011Cc6oC26sT8SRT2Bh6Enuu"}
