{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KWCJrw2RPVNn3eFjdTWAop","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"es-2 is starting up with security disabled (\"Security is disabled\" log message) but it can't find the master node. It's trying to connect to the OLD es-0 and es-1 nodes at IPs 10.244.0.27 and 10.244.0.26.\n\nBut es-0 and es-1 are STILL RUNNING WITH SECURITY ENABLED (they haven't been restarted yet with the new config because the StatefulSet RollingUpdate waits for es-2 to become Ready first).\nSo I'm stuck in a deadlock: es-2 can't join because of the transport protocol mismatch between security-disabled and security-enabled nodes, which means it never becomes Ready, which means the rolling update can't proceed to restart the other two. I need to break this cycle by either forcing all three pods to restart simultaneously or deleting them all at once so they come up together with consistent configurations.\n\nThe safest approach is to delete all three pods directly using kubectl rather than going through the StatefulSet controller, since the data is protected by PVCs anyway. This way they'll all restart fresh with security disabled and can form a cluster without any protocol mismatches.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4517,"cache_read_input_tokens":90864,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4517},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"df7f0fa8-9756-4b8d-b3fa-493542c6ce12","request_id":"req_011Cc6ocNLxFBEJBHfdqWfv3"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KWCJrw2RPVNn3eFjdTWAop","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The RollingUpdate is deadlocked: es-2 runs without security but es-0/es-1 still have security enabled — transport protocol mismatch. I'll force-restart all three pods simultaneously so they all start with the new config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4517,"cache_read_input_tokens":90864,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4517},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348b11d6-5e6f-4791-92b6-393d488f3d3c","uuid":"90f91c64-fed4-4d02-ade4-3be9f2f61958","request_id":"req_011Cc6ocNLxFBEJBHfdqWfv3"}
